                <h1>Understanding Ethnicity: A Brief Overview</h1>
                <p>Ethnicity refers to the shared cultural, linguistic, or ancestral heritage of a group of people. It encompasses traditions, language, and customs, forming a sense of identity among its members. Ethnicity can influence social behaviors, community bonds, and perceptions. Understanding ethnicity fosters appreciation for cultural diversity.</p>
